#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_indexed_array.py:7
msgid "VTKIndexedArray — numpy-compatible mixin for vtkIndexedArray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_indexed_array.py:9
msgid ""
"This module provides the VTKIndexedArray mixin class and registers overrides "
"for all vtkIndexedArray instantiations so that indexed arrays coming from "
"VTK automatically have numpy-compatible operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_indexed_array.py:13
msgid ""
"A vtkIndexedArray provides reindexed access to a base array via an index "
"list: ``result[i] = base_array[index_array[i]]``.  It is used in HyperTree "
"filters and probe filters for zero-copy subset views."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_indexed_array.py:17
msgid ""
"Materialization uses efficient numpy fancy indexing: ``numpy.asarray(base)"
"[numpy.asarray(indexes)]``.  Reductions delegate to the materialized array "
"since there is no closed-form shortcut for arbitrary index subsets."
msgstr ""

